# {{lb|en|transitive|intransitive}} To [[wind]] (something) [[again]].
#* '''2000''', {{w|George RR Martin}}, ''A Storm of Swords'', Bantam 2011, p. 535:
#*: A Myrish crossbowman poked his head out a different window, got off a bolt, and ducked down to '''rewind'''.
# {{lb|en|transitive|intransitive}} To [[wind]] (something) [[back]], now especially of [[cassette]] or video tape, CD, DVD etc.; to [[go back]] on a video or audio recording.
# {{lb|en|figurative}} To [[go]] back or [[think back]] to a previous moment or place, or a previous point in a discourse.
#* '''December 12 2016''', Editorial Team of the {{w|Chicago Tribune}}, ''[http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/opinion/editorials/ct-russia-trump-putin-obama-bush-moscow-kremlin-edit-1213-jm-20161212-story.html Editorial: Trump, Putin and the risks of a reset]''
